""" Logical errors define the flaw in the logic used in the program. The programmer might be using a wrong formula or the design
of the program itself might be wrong. Logical errors are not detected either by the python compiler or the PVM. Hence, the
programmer is solely responsible for correcting the logical errors in the code. """

# An example of a logical error
def population_increment(init_pop):
    init_pop = init_pop * (20/100)
    return(init_pop)
now_pop = population_increment(78000)
print("The present population is",now_pop)

# It is obviously clear that, we have calculated only the increment and, hence the answer we are going to get wont' be correct.
